Miller-Rabin pseudoprimes, form
    U3 = P1 * (K2 * (P1 -1) +1) * (K3 * (P1 -1) +1)
              ^^^^^^ P2 ^^^^^^^   ^^^^^^ P3 ^^^^^^^

Leftover list: we restrict main file to ~100 entries per prime size.

P1 has been selected from a sequence mod M such that if P1,P2,P3 are
all prime, the product passes Miller-Rabin tests with small integers
(chosen as the first N primes).

see
    Arnault: Constructing Carmichael numbers which are strong 
    pseudoprimes to several bases
    J. Symbolic Computation, v. 20, 1995
    core.ac.uk/download/pdf/81930829.pdf
    [accessed 2020-11-13]

Entries include preceding+subsequent-first primes, in case used to
test prime search. MIN.WITNESS=... is the smallest integer which is a
Miller-Rabin witness for U3 being composite.
